        <h4 id="ibanContent">Iban</h4>
        <p>
            The Iban (yi-bɑːn) people is a branch of the Dayak people on the island of Borneo in Southeast Asia. The term
            "Dayak" is believed to be the title given by the westerners to the local poeple of Borneo island.
            The language spoken by them is also called Iban, or <i>jaku Iban</i>, which is a Malayo-Polynesian
            branch of Austronesian language family.<br />
            The Iban people speak basically one language with regional dialects that varies in intonation.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <h5 id="saribasContent">Saribas</h5>
                <p>
                    Saribas is among all the dialects of the Iban language, the most formal, imtermediate, and
                    working dialect. This dialect is taught in school and is mainly spoken around Betong and Saratok.
                </p>
                <br />
